TITLE Custom test vehicle - slender supersonic missile
//
// Hand-built Missile DATCOM-style aero deck for verification.  This
// represents a stylized slender body of revolution:
//   - body length L = 6 m
//   - reference area S = pi * (0.25 m)^2 = 0.196 m^2 (12.5-inch diameter)
//   - reference diameter d = 0.5 m
//   - center of pressure at 0.6 L from the nose -> body is statically
//     stable when CG is forward of 0.6 L
//
// Coefficients chosen so that:
//   - axial force coefficient (drag) peaks around M=1.0 at ~0.6, falls
//     to ~0.3 at high M (typical missile shape)
//   - normal force slope dCN/dalpha ~= 2/rad in subsonic / linear
//     theory, growing slightly with Mach to ~3/rad at supersonic
//   - pitching moment is statically stable: dCm/dalpha < 0 when xcg <
//     center of pressure.  We tabulate Cm directly (not the slope) at
//     the standard reference location xcg_ref = 0.6L = 3.6 m from the
//     nose.  If the actual CG is forward of 3.6 m, Aero adds a
//     restoring term -CN*(xcg_ref - xcg)/refd internally.
//
// Mach axis (10 rows):     0.05, 0.30, 0.60, 0.80, 0.95, 1.10, 1.50, 2.00, 4.00, 8.00
// Alpha axis (7 columns):  0.0, 2.0, 4.0, 6.0, 10.0, 15.0, 20.0 deg

1DIM ca0test_vs_mach
NX1 10  // total axial force coefficient (zero-alpha)
 0.05   0.150
 0.30   0.200
 0.60   0.300
 0.80   0.450
 0.95   0.580
 1.10   0.620
 1.50   0.520
 2.00   0.470
 4.00   0.380
 8.00   0.320

1DIM caatest_vs_mach
NX1 10  // dCa/dalpha (per deg) -- alpha contributes very little to drag
 0.05  -0.0020
 0.30  -0.0025
 0.60  -0.0030
 0.80  -0.0040
 0.95  -0.0050
 1.10  -0.0055
 1.50  -0.0040
 2.00  -0.0025
 4.00  -0.0010
 8.00  -0.0005

1DIM ca0btest_vs_mach
NX1 10  // base bleed correction (small, near-zero for this vehicle)
 0.05  -0.005
 0.30  -0.005
 0.60  -0.005
 0.80  -0.008
 0.95  -0.012
 1.10  -0.015
 1.50  -0.010
 2.00  -0.007
 4.00  -0.003
 8.00  -0.001

2DIM cn0test_vs_mach_alpha
NX1 10 NX2 7  // normal force coefficient
//
// CN = (dCN/dalpha) * alpha for small alpha, with dCN/dalpha growing
// from 2 (subsonic) to 3 (supersonic) per rad.  In deg:
//   subsonic:    dCN/dalpha = 2/rad / 57.3 = 0.0349 /deg
//   supersonic:  dCN/dalpha = 3/rad / 57.3 = 0.0524 /deg
// Then at larger alpha (>10 deg) we add a quadratic term to model
// crossflow drag: CN_total = a1*alpha + a2*alpha*|alpha|/57.3.
// Numbers below are CN evaluated at alpha = 0, 2, 4, 6, 10, 15, 20 deg.
//
 0.05   0.00     0.0   0.070   0.140   0.210   0.360   0.580   0.820
 0.30   2.00     0.0   0.072   0.144   0.218   0.376   0.610   0.870
 0.60   4.00     0.0   0.074   0.150   0.230   0.400   0.660   0.950
 0.80   6.00     0.0   0.078   0.158   0.244   0.430   0.730   1.060
 0.95  10.00     0.0   0.084   0.172   0.270   0.490   0.860   1.270
 1.10  15.00     0.0   0.098   0.200   0.318   0.580   1.020   1.490
 1.50  20.00     0.0   0.105   0.216   0.342   0.620   1.080   1.560
 2.00             0.0   0.107   0.220   0.346   0.620   1.060   1.520
 4.00             0.0   0.103   0.210   0.330   0.580   0.980   1.400
 8.00             0.0   0.100   0.200   0.310   0.540   0.920   1.300

2DIM clm0test_vs_mach_alpha
NX1 10 NX2 7  // pitching moment about xcg_ref = 0.6 L = 3.6 m from nose
//
// Center of pressure xcp is at 0.55L (subsonic) -> 0.65L (supersonic).
// With xcg_ref = 0.6L, Cm relative to xcg_ref is:
//   Cm(at xcg_ref) = CN * (xcp - xcg_ref) / d
// where xcp moves aftward with Mach: subsonic xcp = 0.55L, so
//   (xcp - xcg_ref)/d = (0.55 - 0.60)*6/0.5 = -0.6 (statically stable
//   when nominal CG is at xcg_ref, body wants to weathercock)
//
// Supersonic xcp = 0.65L:
//   (xcp - xcg_ref)/d = (0.65 - 0.60)*6/0.5 = +0.6 (statically unstable
//   when nominal CG is at xcg_ref -- needs control!)
//
// In practice, by xcg_1 we want body to be statically stable.  For
// this test vehicle xcg_1 = 3.0 m which is forward of xcp at both
// subsonic and supersonic Mach, so the body IS stable when fuel is
// depleted.  We tabulate raw Cm at xcg_ref:
//
 0.05   0.00     0.0  -0.042  -0.084  -0.126  -0.216  -0.348  -0.492
 0.30   2.00     0.0  -0.043  -0.086  -0.131  -0.226  -0.366  -0.522
 0.60   4.00     0.0  -0.044  -0.090  -0.138  -0.240  -0.396  -0.570
 0.80   6.00     0.0  -0.039  -0.079  -0.122  -0.215  -0.365  -0.530
 0.95  10.00     0.0  -0.025  -0.052  -0.081  -0.147  -0.258  -0.381
 1.10  15.00     0.0   0.010   0.020   0.032   0.058   0.102   0.149
 1.50  20.00     0.0   0.052   0.108   0.171   0.310   0.540   0.780
 2.00             0.0   0.064   0.132   0.208   0.372   0.636   0.912
 4.00             0.0   0.062   0.126   0.198   0.348   0.588   0.840
 8.00             0.0   0.060   0.120   0.186   0.324   0.552   0.780

1DIM clmqtest_vs_mach
NX1 10  // pitch damping derivative (per rad) -- moderate, slightly
        // less than Zipfel's SLV (which has more body area for damping)
 0.05  -0.180
 0.30  -0.190
 0.60  -0.230
 0.80  -0.280
 0.95  -0.340
 1.10  -0.380
 1.50  -0.310
 2.00  -0.290
 4.00  -0.260
 8.00  -0.240
